article.headline: Diallo scores 14, Merrimack defeats Saint Francis Red Flash 71-60
article.description: — Samba Diallo scored 14 points as Merrimack beat Saint Francis (Pennsylvania) 71-60 on Thursday night.
article.linkText: Diallo scores 14, Merrimack defeats Saint Francis Red Flash 71-60
article.story: NORTH ANDOVER, Mass. -- — Samba Diallo scored 14 points as Merrimack beat Saint Francis (Pennsylvania) 71-60 on Thursday night. Diallo also had six rebounds and three steals for the Warriors (18-10, 12-2 Northeast Conference). Adam Clark scored 13 points and added five assists and three steals. Jordan Derkack had 11 points and was 4 of 10 shooting, and went 3 for 6 from the line. The Warriors picked up their ninth straight win. Eli Wilborn finished with 16 points for the Red Flash (8-19, 3-11). Gestin Liberis added 14 points, 10 rebounds and three blocks for Saint Francis. Aaron Talbert also recorded 10 points. ------ The Associated Press created this story using technology provided by Data Skrive and data from Sportradar.
